Please step aside.

268
00:32:09,210 --> 00:32:10,378
Get up.

269
00:32:10,378 --> 00:32:12,171
Great work, Sir.

270
00:32:42,427 --> 00:32:44,295
Want some water?

271
00:32:58,276 --> 00:33:02,563
You inhaled a lot of smoke, but luckily your lungs are okay.

272
00:33:03,932 --> 00:33:08,411
You have light burns here and there, but they're not severe.

273
00:33:09,813 --> 00:33:13,574
We'll have to keep a close watch for a while,

274
00:33:14,467 --> 00:33:18,470
but you can drink and eat.

275
00:33:19,197 --> 00:33:20,665
You want water?

276
00:33:23,701 --> 00:33:27,738
If not water, you want juice instead?

277
00:33:30,959 --> 00:33:32,919
Someone came to visit

278
00:33:32,919 --> 00:33:35,096
while you were asleep.

279
00:33:41,219 --> 00:33:43,496
Stop right there!

280
00:33:43,496 --> 00:33:46,449
The shot is to not make you sick.

281
00:33:46,449 --> 00:33:48,768
It scared you?

282
00:33:48,768 --> 00:33:51,287
Even your sister got it.

283
00:33:51,287 --> 00:33:53,565
- I don't want to!
- I know.

284
00:33:53,565 --> 00:33:56,200
Mommy will give you a piggyback.

285
00:33:58,361 --> 00:33:59,662
There.

286
00:34:26,139 --> 00:34:31,540
She came by with the box of juice earlier.

287
00:34:32,270 --> 00:34:34,438
She sends her thanks.

288
00:34:36,691 --> 00:34:39,452
Are the other ones okay, too?

289
00:34:42,522 --> 00:34:44,491
- You!
- Ow!

290
00:34:44,491 --> 00:34:46,868
What on earth are you doing?

291
00:34:46,868 --> 00:34:49,387
What's wrong with you? I'm a patient!

292
00:34:49,387 --> 00:34:53,124
I sent you up there to save people, and you come back hurt?

293
00:34:53,124 --> 00:34:56,461
- Stop it, go away!
- Calm down, please.

294
00:34:56,461 --> 00:34:58,261
Stop right there!

295
00:34:58,262 --> 00:35:01,290
How could you worry your old grandma like this?

296
00:35:01,290 --> 00:35:04,928
Where is she? Come here right now!

297
00:35:04,928 --> 00:35:08,629
Hey!

298
00:35:18,525 --> 00:35:19,734
Did she leave?

299
00:35:19,734 --> 00:35:22,962
She's no joke!

300
00:35:22,962 --> 00:35:25,073
She fell asleep on your bed.

301
00:35:25,073 --> 00:35:28,593
I was wondering who you took after. It's your grandma.

302
00:35:28,593 --> 00:35:30,194
Quiet.

303
00:35:30,987 --> 00:35:33,056
Drink up.

304
00:35:33,056 --> 00:35:34,757
Thanks.

305
00:35:38,853 --> 00:35:44,072
We found... Lee Se Wook's body.

306
00:35:45,051 --> 00:35:48,012
All his articles were burned by the fire,

307
00:35:48,012 --> 00:35:50,014
and it was impossible to do a DNA test,

308
00:35:50,014 --> 00:35:54,435
but the teeth matched his dental records.

309
00:35:54,435 --> 00:35:57,897
Considering that his skeleton was fractured here and there,

310
00:35:57,897 --> 00:36:02,977
the police concluded that he fell from the cliff and died.

311
00:36:04,028 --> 00:36:07,415
Then... it's all over now.

312
00:36:18,459 --> 00:36:22,130
These are the incidents you've been seeing.

313
00:36:22,130 --> 00:36:24,181
Why did you write them down?

314
00:36:25,300 --> 00:36:28,736
Why did I see only these cases?

315
00:36:30,622 --> 00:36:31,764
What do you mean?

316
00:36:31,764 --> 00:36:34,459
There have been 25 deaths that occurred

317
00:36:34,459 --> 00:36:38,521
on Jirisan after Hyeon Su died.

318
00:36:38,521 --> 00:36:43,117
But why did I only see these?

319
00:36:44,193 --> 00:36:45,737
I looked into the 20 cases...

320
00:36:45,737 --> 00:36:48,381
that I didn't foresee.

321
00:36:48,381 --> 00:36:50,658
Except for Geum Rye, all the other cases were

322
00:36:50,658 --> 00:36:54,762
simple accidents, or hikers who already

323
00:36:54,762 --> 00:36:57,620
suffered from heart disease.

324
00:36:59,709 --> 00:37:01,978
Then the ones you saw...?

325
00:37:01,978 --> 00:37:04,355
Murders disguised as accidents.

326
00:37:04,355 --> 00:37:08,893
That was the case with the poisoned yogurt drinks and potato bombs.

327
00:37:09,636 --> 00:37:12,563
Other cases, too, most likely.

328
00:37:17,702 --> 00:37:22,440
Here, an old rope on a restricted trail broke, carrying the lady with it.

329
00:37:22,440 --> 00:37:24,825
I also saw the rope breaking.

330
00:37:31,799 --> 00:37:34,786
Someone could have cut it on purpose in advance.

331
00:37:34,786 --> 00:37:36,387
Same with the next case.

332
00:37:36,387 --> 00:37:38,072
He was climbing a snowy mountain.

333
00:37:38,072 --> 00:37:40,083
And he fell off and died.

334
00:37:40,083 --> 00:37:42,443
There were footprints of two people.

335
00:37:42,443 --> 00:37:45,088
Someone must have pushed the other from behind.

336
00:37:45,088 --> 00:37:48,508
There was a hiking pole next to the cliff.

337
00:37:48,508 --> 00:37:53,488
Someone must have tricked the man with it and pushed him from behind.

338
00:37:53,488 --> 00:37:56,933
You mean Se Wook killed all these people?

339
00:37:56,933 --> 00:37:59,360
Se Wook wasn't alone.

340
00:38:00,328 --> 00:38:02,822
I think he had an accomplice.

341
00:38:07,193 --> 00:38:09,812
That fire in the storage...

342
00:38:09,812 --> 00:38:14,200
Someone trapped us in there and set the fire on purpose.

343
00:38:14,200 --> 00:38:15,676
Did you tell the police?

344
00:38:15,676 --> 00:38:18,229
I did, but there was no evidence.

345
00:38:18,229 --> 00:38:22,709
They checked the storage building, but the door wasn't locked.

346
00:38:22,709 --> 00:38:25,386
And there was no sign of arson.

347
00:38:26,879 --> 00:38:29,132
But I'm certain.

348
00:38:29,132 --> 00:38:32,059
Someone was targeting me.

349
00:38:33,911 --> 00:38:36,578
Who? And why?

350
00:38:37,115 --> 00:38:40,435
I went to see Se Wook before he died.

351
00:38:40,435 --> 00:38:45,189
I asked him about the yogurt and potato bombs, which caught him off guard.

352
00:38:45,189 --> 00:38:48,200
He must have thought I was onto something.

353
00:38:49,168 --> 00:38:50,336
But...

354
00:38:50,336 --> 00:38:52,455
Someone searched my room.

355
00:38:53,089 --> 00:38:55,550
My desk at the ranger station, too.

356
00:38:55,550 --> 00:38:58,953
The file folders were in the wrong order.

357
00:38:58,953 --> 00:39:01,664
I don't know who,

358
00:39:01,664 --> 00:39:03,799
but someone's targeting me.

359
00:39:04,725 --> 00:39:06,736
Since I'm not that dead this time,

360
00:39:07,353 --> 00:39:10,297
that person will try to kill me once more.

361
00:39:10,965 --> 00:39:12,275
Let's go and tell the police everything.

362
00:39:12,275 --> 00:39:14,184
I'll help you.

363
00:39:15,528 --> 00:39:17,655
Like you said before,

364
00:39:17,655 --> 00:39:19,982
no one will believe us.

365
00:39:22,810 --> 00:39:27,106
But you're in danger. We must do everything we can.

366
00:39:27,106 --> 00:39:28,791
But I'm relieved.

367
00:39:28,791 --> 00:39:31,110
That it's me, not someone else.

368
00:39:31,110 --> 00:39:32,086
What?

369
00:39:32,086 --> 00:39:34,363
The murderer doesn't know

370
00:39:34,363 --> 00:39:37,249
the secret we're hiding.

371
00:39:39,535 --> 00:39:42,513
The next time the murderer comes for me,

372
00:39:42,513 --> 00:39:44,280
the mountain...

373
00:39:45,833 --> 00:39:48,352
will show me something again.

374
00:39:48,352 --> 00:39:50,888
It'll show me what will happen.

375
00:39:52,715 --> 00:39:56,844
We can catch the murderer then.

376
00:39:56,844 --> 00:40:00,772
Even if we fail, we'll find evidence

377
00:40:00,773 --> 00:40:03,592
and report to the police.

378
00:40:03,592 --> 00:40:06,354
You can get hurt.

379
00:40:07,547 --> 00:40:09,172
Who are we?

380
00:40:09,172 --> 00:40:12,576
The needle and the thread of Jirisan.

381
00:40:12,576 --> 00:40:15,154
We'll get the person for sure.

382
00:40:17,515 --> 00:40:19,391
Okay.

383
00:40:19,391 --> 00:40:20,976
Just promise me one thing.

384
00:40:20,976 --> 00:40:24,646
From now on, wherever you go and whatever you do, move with me.

385
00:40:24,646 --> 00:40:28,973
If you get into trouble by yourself, I won't forgive you.

386
00:40:28,973 --> 00:40:33,755
I'll always stick close to you except when I'm sleeping or using the toilet.

387
00:40:33,755 --> 00:40:34,965
I'm not joking.

388
00:40:34,965 --> 00:40:37,151
Neither am I.

389
00:40:42,623 --> 00:40:46,485
We got lucky this time, too.

390
00:40:47,904 --> 00:40:53,489
Indeed a big wildfire broke out, but no casualties.

391
00:40:53,489 --> 00:40:57,669
You saved... those kids.

392
00:41:10,120 --> 00:41:13,610
[Senior Yi Kang]

393
00:41:21,550 --> 00:41:24,410
[Senior Yi Kang]

394
00:41:28,486 --> 00:41:29,504
Yes.

395
00:41:29,504 --> 00:41:32,397
Where are you? You haven't been around.

396
00:41:32,397 --> 00:41:33,840
I'm in the bathroom.

397
00:41:33,840 --> 00:41:36,310
All right. Come out quick.

398
00:41:43,935 --> 00:41:46,995
Hurry up. It's about to start.

399
00:41:46,995 --> 00:41:49,215
Yes, coming.

400
00:41:54,737 --> 00:41:56,830
It's starting.

401
00:41:58,330 --> 00:42:03,190
[Conversations With Area Residents]

402
00:42:09,585 --> 00:42:11,562
We're here.

403
00:42:16,108 --> 00:42:17,901
Hello!

404
00:42:17,901 --> 00:42:22,172
Come on. The food will get cold.

405
00:42:22,865 --> 00:42:24,575
Come on.

406
00:42:30,289 --> 00:42:32,115
Hello.

407
00:42:32,115 --> 00:42:34,070
Let's go inside.

408
00:42:36,237 --> 00:42:37,904
Welcome. Please come in.

409
00:42:37,904 --> 00:42:41,049
Hello. Please come in.

410
00:42:43,744 --> 00:42:45,830
Everyone's here.

411
00:42:46,806 --> 00:42:48,673
New shoes?

412
00:42:48,673 --> 00:42:51,568
If you ever come to Jirisan,

413
00:42:51,568 --> 00:42:54,905
come see the sunrise of the Cheonwangbong Peak.

414
00:42:54,905 --> 00:42:59,301
If you truly wish to come to Jirisan...
(2019: Conversation With Local Residents)

415
00:42:59,301 --> 00:43:03,663
you shall have a humble heart like a grain of sand on a sandy beach

416
00:43:03,663 --> 00:43:07,642
in the shadow of the verdant mountain cast over the Seomjingang River.

417
00:43:07,642 --> 00:43:11,162
If you wish to see the cliffs and dead trees of Yeonhwabong Peak,

418
00:43:11,162 --> 00:43:16,151
only those who often think of suicide shall come, to take time to reflect on themselves.

419
00:43:16,151 --> 00:43:18,970
Nevertheless, if you wish to come to Jirisan,

420
00:43:18,970 --> 00:43:22,849
please come anytime without any preparation.

421
00:43:22,849 --> 00:43:25,769
Unlike you, who are capricious every day,

422
00:43:25,769 --> 00:43:30,532
Jirisan keeps changing, but it's always the same as the first,

423
00:43:30,532 --> 00:43:32,459
so if your life is tolerable, never come here.

424
00:43:32,459 --> 00:43:34,894
We need to change the air.

425
00:43:34,894 --> 00:43:37,481
I agree. Definitely.

426
00:43:40,651 --> 00:43:44,279
♫ That's how life is ♫

427
00:43:44,279 --> 00:43:47,658
♫ Everyone comes empty-handed ♫

428
00:43:47,658 --> 00:43:51,828
♫ And leave a life story like novel ♫

429
00:43:51,828 --> 00:43:59,720
♫  The memories that I erased  ♫

430
00:43:59,720 --> 00:44:07,670
♫ in white are colored with yellow ♫

431
00:44:07,670 --> 00:44:12,870
♫ Before we know it ♫

432
00:44:12,870 --> 00:44:23,820
♫ It's drawn bigger with blue light ♫

433
00:44:23,820 --> 00:44:31,650
♫ Sometimes it turns red ♫

434
00:44:31,650 --> 00:44:38,640
♫ But even if you make me sad ♫

435
00:44:38,640 --> 00:44:43,920
♫ It came off white ♫

436
00:44:43,920 --> 00:44:45,960
[Nature, Our Future!]

437
00:44:45,960 --> 00:44:50,830
[2020]

438
00:44:50,830 --> 00:44:57,470
[Monthly Meeting for Second Half of 2020]

439
00:45:00,750 --> 00:45:06,119
The barrier-free trail to be open next week is accessible by wheelchairs,

440
00:45:06,119 --> 00:45:11,099
so people with limited mobility such as the elderly and the disabled can use the park

441
00:45:11,099 --> 00:45:14,594
more conveniently.

442
00:45:14,594 --> 00:45:17,022
Is the safety secured?

443
00:45:17,022 --> 00:45:18,565
Yes.

444
00:45:18,565 --> 00:45:20,734
The average incline is one-eighteenth,

445
00:45:20,734 --> 00:45:25,130
and the average width of the trail is 1.5 meters, so it's pretty safe.

446
00:45:25,130 --> 00:45:29,259
Put up the notices and have everything ready before opening.

447
00:45:29,259 --> 00:45:31,594
If there's any little thing that needs improvement,

448
00:45:31,594 --> 00:45:34,055
file a report right away.

449
00:45:34,055 --> 00:45:36,033
Yes, sir.

450
00:45:41,730 --> 00:45:47,730
[Monthly Meeting for Second Half of 2020]

451
00:45:47,730 --> 00:45:49,530
Seo Yi Kang.

452
00:45:52,250 --> 00:45:53,908
Are you okay?

453
00:45:53,908 --> 00:45:55,618
Yup. I'm fine.

454
00:45:55,618 --> 00:45:58,605
Senior, let me know if we can help you with anything.

455
00:45:58,605 --> 00:46:00,549
Sure.

456
00:46:11,119 --> 00:46:17,839
So... one of them could be the criminal, huh?

457
00:46:17,839 --> 00:46:21,069
I know it's tough, climbing up the mountain on your days off,

458
00:46:21,069 --> 00:46:23,046
but please keep it a secret for now.

459
00:46:23,046 --> 00:46:24,547
Of course!

460
00:46:24,547 --> 00:46:28,986
I might be careless, but I can keep a secret well.

461
00:46:30,246 --> 00:46:33,473
Sorry, I keep dragging you into danger.

462
00:46:33,473 --> 00:46:35,809
No, don't say such a thing.

463
00:46:35,809 --> 00:46:37,795
I'm a ranger, too.

464
00:46:37,795 --> 00:46:44,207
And isn't what we do as a ranger always dangerous?

465
00:46:46,153 --> 00:46:50,700
Isn't our job always dangerous?

466
00:47:02,153 --> 00:47:04,012
Senior?

467
00:47:06,483 --> 00:47:11,369
Our job... is to come back safely from a dangerous place.

468
00:47:11,369 --> 00:47:14,820
So don't get hurt and come back safe.

469
00:47:16,876 --> 00:47:20,030
Okay!

470
00:47:26,093 --> 00:47:27,710
2 km point.

471
00:47:27,710 --> 00:47:30,004
Right here.

472
00:47:30,004 --> 00:47:33,133
Yangseokbong Peak.

473
00:47:33,133 --> 00:47:38,860
2 km point from the Hurricane Lily habitat in Dure Forest.

474
00:47:52,219 --> 00:47:54,512
There are things that you need to be cautious about.

475
00:47:54,512 --> 00:47:57,432
The murderer killed people in different ways.

476
00:47:57,432 --> 00:48:00,185
Like cutting the old rope attached to a rock

477
00:48:00,185 --> 00:48:02,170
or placing a poisoned yogurt.

478
00:48:02,170 --> 00:48:05,273
If anything looks suspicious, take caution.

479
00:48:05,273 --> 00:48:08,300
Okay.

480
00:49:22,084 --> 00:49:23,351
Haedong Ranger Station.

481
00:49:23,351 --> 00:49:25,562
Yi Kang? It's me. Are you busy?

482
00:49:25,562 --> 00:49:29,332
- What is it?
- I think you should come...

483
00:49:30,484 --> 00:49:33,945
- Is this it?
- Yeah.

484
00:49:33,945 --> 00:49:36,355
We caught them while on patrol and brought them here,

485
00:49:36,355 --> 00:49:39,301
but there are way too many kinds that we don't know.

486
00:49:40,010 --> 00:49:42,388
This really is a lot.

487
00:49:43,664 --> 00:49:45,840
I know.

488
00:49:45,840 --> 00:49:50,545
Apparently, they can only go up on spiritless days, so they took as much as they could.

489
00:49:50,545 --> 00:49:53,756
What are spiritless days?

490
00:49:53,756 --> 00:49:56,526
The days with 9 and 0 on the lunar calendar.

491
00:49:56,526 --> 00:50:00,371
That's when the spirits or ghosts that disturb people's work

492
00:50:00,372 --> 00:50:02,374
don't come out.

493
00:50:57,512 --> 00:50:59,347
Wait a sec!

494
00:51:00,883 --> 00:51:03,284
I'm sorry I kept collecting,

495
00:51:03,284 --> 00:51:05,912
but I've been doing that all my life.

496
00:51:05,912 --> 00:51:08,931
I can't just stop because I'm scared of a ghost.

497
00:51:08,931 --> 00:51:11,517
You mean the ghost...

498
00:51:11,517 --> 00:51:13,603
you told me you saw before?

499
00:51:13,603 --> 00:51:16,381
All herb collectors know about that ghost.

500
00:51:16,381 --> 00:51:20,009
We all went up on a spiritless day since we're all scared of the ghost.

501
00:51:20,009 --> 00:51:24,306
Whoever saw that ghost has died.

502
00:51:24,306 --> 00:51:29,242
So the story you told me before, it's really true?

503
00:51:29,242 --> 00:51:30,520
I'm serious.

504
00:51:30,520 --> 00:51:33,106
Mr. Jang who died in Moojin Valley 3 months ago

505
00:51:33,106 --> 00:51:34,716
also told me before he died

506
00:51:34,716 --> 00:51:37,527
that he saw a man in a bloody uniform.

507
00:51:37,527 --> 00:51:38,986
Not just him.

508
00:51:38,986 --> 00:51:44,867
Gi Yeong, who was going to his ancestral grave and died in Oerae Valley, also said he saw him.

509
00:51:44,867 --> 00:51:49,038
And Mr. Hwang, who nearly died in Jeonmuk Valley because the rope broke,

510
00:51:49,038 --> 00:51:51,708
saw him, too.

511
00:51:52,651 --> 00:51:55,730
I saw a guy with a ranger's uniform.

512
00:51:58,532 --> 00:52:01,900
His hands and clothes were covered in blood.

513
00:53:28,555 --> 00:53:33,393
You had an accident in Jeonmuk Valley?

514
00:53:33,393 --> 00:53:37,605
It was the road I took every day, but the rope broke and I nearly died.

515
00:53:37,605 --> 00:53:41,692
If it weren't for the hiker passing by, I would have died.

516
00:53:41,692 --> 00:53:47,394
I heard you met someone in a uniform before the accident.

517
00:53:50,477 --> 00:53:52,546
Was it him?

518
00:53:54,523 --> 00:53:56,499
Who is this?

519
00:53:56,499 --> 00:53:58,000
Do you know him?

520
00:53:58,000 --> 00:53:59,560
Did you see this man?

521
00:53:59,560 --> 00:54:02,104
It wasn't a man.

522
00:54:02,104 --> 00:54:05,642
It was a ghost. A grim reaper.

523
00:54:06,510 --> 00:54:12,411
Whoever saw that ghost... has died.

524
00:56:21,080 --> 00:56:23,090
[Lee Da Won]

525
00:57:33,350 --> 00:57:35,980
[Support Center for Broad Area Travel]

526
00:58:08,220 --> 00:58:11,660
[Jirisan National Park]

527
00:58:22,870 --> 00:58:26,300
[Lee Da Won]

528
00:59:06,920 --> 00:59:10,480
[Ranger]

529
00:59:44,055 --> 00:59:46,940
You scared me.

530
00:59:46,940 --> 00:59:49,390
What are you doing here?

531
01:00:14,930 --> 01:00:23,320
♫ Shine along, the leaves they dance and speak ♫

532
01:00:23,320 --> 01:00:31,950
♫ and sway... and your colors they remind me ♫

533
